{"repo": "sezanzeb/input-remapper", "pull_number": 1212, "instance_id": "sezanzeb__input-remapper-1212", "issue_numbers": [1207], "base_commit": "1bfa95b7720455db75fd0de2c408fb4c7e507b8a", "patch": "diff --git a/inputremapper/bin/input_remapper_control.py b/inputremapper/bin/input_remapper_control.py\nindex f2c22d328..1fde6e6a6 100755\n--- a/inputremapper/bin/input_remapper_control.py\n+++ b/inputremapper/bin/input_remapper_control.py\n@@ -267,11 +267,11 @@ def _autoload(self, device: str) -> None:\n         # for all devices.\n         if device is None:\n             logger.info(\"Autoloading all\")\n-            self.daemon.autoload(timeout=10)\n+            self.daemon.autoload(timeout=10000)\n         else:\n             group = self._require_group(device)\n             logger.info(\"Asking daemon to autoload for %s\", device)\n-            self.daemon.autoload_single(group.key, timeout=2)\n+            self.daemon.autoload_single(group.key, timeout=2000)\n \n     def internals(self, command: str, debug: True) -> None:\n         \"\"\"Methods that are needed to get the gui to work and that require root.\ndiff --git a/inputremapper/daemon.py b/inputremapper/daemon.py\nindex 9484dbf54..ba801c77d 100644\n--- a/inputremapper/daemon.py\n+++ b/inputremapper/daemon.py\n@@ -23,7 +23,6 @@\n https://github.com/dasbus-project/dasbus/tree/master/examples/03_helloworld\n \"\"\"\n \n-\n import atexit\n import json\n import os\n@@ -60,8 +59,8 @@\n     message_bus=SESSION_BUS,\n )\n \n-# timeout in seconds\n-BUS_TIMEOUT = 10\n+# timeout in milliseconds\n+BUS_TIMEOUT = 10000\n \n \n class AutoloadHistory:\n@@ -269,7 +268,7 @@ def connect(cls, fallback: bool = True) -> Optional[DaemonProxy]:\n         if UserUtils.user != \"root\":\n             config_path = PathUtils.get_config_path()\n             logger.debug('Telling service about \"%s\"', config_path)\n-            proxy.set_config_dir(PathUtils.get_config_path(), timeout=2)\n+            proxy.set_config_dir(PathUtils.get_config_path(), timeout=2000)\n \n         return proxy\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Autoload results in intermittent error: TimeoutError: The DBus call timeout was reached.\n```\nConnected to the service\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/usr/bin/input-remapper-control\", line 49, in <module>\n    InputRemapperControlBin.main(InputRemapperControlBin.parse_args())\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/inputremapper/bin/input_remapper_control.py\", line 116, in main\n    daemon = Daemon.connect(fallback=False)\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/inputremapper/daemon.py\", line 272, in connect\n    proxy.set_config_dir(PathUtils.get_config_path(), timeout=2)\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/dasbus/client/handler.py\", line 450, in _call_method\n    return self._get_method_reply(\n           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^\n      self._client.sync_call,\n      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n      *args,\n      ^^^^^^\n      **kwargs,\n      ^^^^^^^^^\n   )\n   ^\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/dasbus/client/handler.py\", line 483, in _get_method_reply\n    return self._handle_method_error(error)\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/dasbus/client/handler.py\", line 513, in _handle_method_error\n    raise TimeoutError(\n      \"The DBus call timeout was reached.\"\n    ) from None\nTimeoutError: The DBus call timeout was reached.\n```\n\n\n**System Information and logs**\n\n1. `input-remapper-control --version` -> `input-remapper 2.2.0 b66def981fd758faa718616f30d40d94839edbb4 https://github.com/sezanzeb/input-remapper` & `python-evdev 1.9.2`\n2. which linux distro (ubuntu 20.04, manjaro, etc.) ->  CachyOS\n3. which desktop environment (gnome, plasma, xfce4, etc.) -> Plasma Wayland\n4. `sudo ls -l /proc/1/exe` to check if you are using systemd -> `lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 0 Nov 12  2025 /proc/1/exe -> /usr/lib/systemd/systemd`\n5. `cat ~/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json` to see if the \"autoload\" config is written correctly\n```\n\"version\": \"2.2.0\",\n\"autoload\": {\n\"ELECOM TrackBall Mouse HUGE TrackBall\": \"default\",\n\"SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard\": \"default\",\n\"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\": \"default\",\n\"HUION Huion Tablet Pad\": \"default\",\n\"SteelSeries SteelSeries Rival 500 Gaming Mouse\": \"default\"\n}\n}\n```\n6. `systemctl status input-remapper -n 50` the service has to be running\n```\n\u25cf input-remapper.service - Service to inject keycodes without the GUI application\nLoaded: loaded (/usr/lib/systemd/system/input-remapper.service; enabled; preset: disabled)\nActive: active (running) since Wed 2025-11-12 23:07:28 NZDT; 7h left\nInvocation: fd19f918897e4caf88186b35b5af8ad1\nMain PID: 1079 (python3)\nTasks: 6 (limit: 38267)\nMemory: 29.7M (peak: 87.1M, swap: 31.4M, swap peak: 43.4M)\nNov 12 15:16:45 orion input-remapper-service[3637534]: Starting injecting the preset for \"SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard\"\nNov 12 15:16:45 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:45 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Request to start injecting for \"SteelSeries SteelSeries Rival 500 Gaming Mouse\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loading preset from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/presets/SteelSeries SteelSeries Rival 500 Gaming Mouse/helldivers2.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Stopping injecting keycodes for group \"SteelSeries SteelSeries Rival 500 Gaming Mouse\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[3637697]: Starting injecting the preset for \"SteelSeries SteelSeries Rival 500 Gaming Mouse\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[2514047]: read loop for /dev/input/event5 stopped\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Request to start injecting for \"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loading preset from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/presets/Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX/helldivers2.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Stopping injecting keycodes for group \"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\"\nNov 12 15:16:46 orion input-remapper-service[3637898]: Starting injecting the preset for \"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\"\nNov 12 15:16:56 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:56 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:56 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Stopping injecting keycodes for group \"SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard\"\nNov 12 15:16:56 orion input-remapper-service[3637534]: read loop for /dev/input/event2 stopped\nNov 12 15:16:56 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:56 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:56 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Request to autoload for \"SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Found \"input-remapper Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX forwarded\", \"input-remapper SteelSeries SteelSeries Rival 500 Gaming Mouse forw>\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Autoloading for \"SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Request to start injecting for \"SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loading preset from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/presets/SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard/default.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: ERROR: Tried to load non-existing preset \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/presets/SEMITEK USB-HID Gaming Keyboard/default.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Stopping injecting keycodes for group \"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[3637898]: read loop for /dev/input/event7 stopped\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:57 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:58 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Request to autoload for \"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\"\nNov 12 15:16:58 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Autoloading for \"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\"\nNov 12 15:16:58 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Request to start injecting for \"Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX\"\nNov 12 15:16:58 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loading preset from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/presets/Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX/default.json\"\nNov 12 15:16:58 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: ERROR: Tried to load non-existing preset \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/presets/Logitech Logitech Driving Force EX/default.json\"\nNov 12 15:20:58 orion input-remapper-service[1079]: Loaded config from \"/home/USER/.config/input-remapper-2/config.json\"\n```\n\n7. `journalctl -b | grep input-remapper`**Testing the setup**1. `input-remapper-control --command hello`\n```\nConnected to the service\nDaemon answered with \"hello\"\nDone\n```\n\n8. `sudo pkill -f input-remapper-service && sudo input-remapper-service -d & sleep 2 && input-remapper-control --command autoload`, are your keys mapped now? *It's intermittent.*\n9. `sudo udevadm control --log-priority=debug && sudo udevadm control --reload-rules && journalctl -f | grep input-remapper`, now plug in the device that should autoload. *It's intermittent.*\n", "hints_text": "Where exactly did you get the above stack trace from?\nAre you able to reliably reproduce the issue, if yes, how?\n\nDid this happen right after you updated input-remapper?\n> Where exactly did you get the above stack trace from?\n\nI have a script that checks for device profiles matching specific application names and automatically activates them via `input-remapper-control`, then autoloads the device when the binary closes.\n\nYou're correct in that I didn't see this error in `input-remapper`'s systemd log. Took me a while to figure out why the profile wasn't reverting correctly. The error shows up in the `input-seeker`'s systemd log when it tries to trigger the autoload.\n\n> Are you able to reliably reproduce the issue, if yes, how?\n\nUnfortunately no. I can `nano binary_name` then exit to force loading/autoload over and over without this occuring, then it randomly will and the binary_name profile remains active.\n \n> Did this happen right after you updated input-remapper?\n\nIt's a fresh OS install with input-remapper installed ~2 days ago and not updated since.\n3 days ago I switched input-remapper from pydbus to dasbus https://github.com/sezanzeb/input-remapper/commit/77e9f48b03e53f23693ee4637dd2680fad3266b0 https://github.com/sezanzeb/input-remapper/pull/1201\n\nCould you please try to increase the timeout to 10 seconds in\n\n```\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/inputremapper/daemon.py\", line 272, in connect\n    proxy.set_config_dir(PathUtils.get_config_path(), timeout=2)\n```\n\n?\n\nI also just now got a timeout error for the \"hello\" command, but can't reproduce it anymore\n> Could you please try to increase the timeout to 10 seconds in\n> \n> ```\n>   File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/inputremapper/daemon.py\", line 272, in connect\n>     proxy.set_config_dir(PathUtils.get_config_path(), timeout=2)\n> ```\n> \n> ?\n\nI went straight to `timeout=30` when I first saw the error. When I got it to error again, it seemingly errored immediately.\n\n> Did this happen right after you updated input-remapper?\n\nI can confirm that my autoload doesn't work after the update\nDoes `input-remapper-control --command autoload` reproduce it reliably for you?\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Where exactly did you get the above stack trace from?\nAre you able to reliably reproduce the issue, if yes, how?\n\nDid this happen right after you updated input-remapper?\n> Where exactly did you get the above stack trace from?\n\nI have a script that checks for device profiles matching specific application names and automatically activates them via `input-remapper-control`, then autoloads the device when the binary closes.\n\nYou're correct in that I didn't see this error in `input-remapper`'s systemd log. Took me a while to figure out why the profile wasn't reverting correctly. The error shows up in the `input-seeker`'s systemd log when it tries to trigger the autoload.\n\n> Are you able to reliably reproduce the issue, if yes, how?\n\nUnfortunately no. I can `nano binary_name` then exit to force loading/autoload over and over without this occuring, then it randomly will and the binary_name profile remains active.\n \n> Did this happen right after you updated input-remapper?\n\nIt's a fresh OS install with input-remapper installed ~2 days ago and not updated since.\n3 days ago I switched input-remapper from pydbus to dasbus https://github.com/sezanzeb/input-remapper/commit/77e9f48b03e53f23693ee4637dd2680fad3266b0 https://github.com/sezanzeb/input-remapper/pull/1201\n\nCould you please try to increase the timeout to 10 seconds in\n\n```\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/inputremapper/daemon.py\", line 272, in connect\n    proxy.set_config_dir(PathUtils.get_config_path(), timeout=2)\n```\n\n?\n\nI also just now got a timeout error for the \"hello\" command, but can't reproduce it anymore\n> Could you please try to increase the timeout to 10 seconds in\n> \n> ```\n>   File \"/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/inputremapper/daemon.py\", line 272, in connect\n>     proxy.set_config_dir(PathUtils.get_config_path(), timeout=2)\n> ```\n> \n> ?\n\nI went straight to `timeout=30` when I first saw the error. When I got it to error again, it seemingly errored immediately.\n\n> Did this happen right after you updated input-remapper?\n\nI can confirm that my autoload doesn't work after the update\nDoes `input-remapper-control --command autoload` reproduce it reliably for you?\nThe timeout is in milliseconds in dasbus. Should be fixed now.\nI am running input-remapper 2.2.0 b66def981fd758faa718616f30d40d94839edbb4 under arch, and am still facing this issue reliably on startup when running\n```\ninput-remapper-control --command autoload`\n```\nI have that line in my zshlogin, but there it fails 100% as far as I can tell.\nWhen running it from a terminal later on it tends to fail once or twice (always DBus timeout), and then work.\n\nEdit:\nLooking at git here, it seems like the fix for this was merged before the 2.2.0 release and is included?\nYeah that commit is too old, you'll need to update to the latest source, the DBus timeout is fixed in 4d6af54\n\nThe 2.2.0 release still uses pydbus. The switch to dasbus has not been part of a formal release yet\nAhh I see, my bad. I wasn't sure why that commit hash was after the version lol.\nFunny enough, the \"input-remapper-git\" in the arch user repository is newer than my local version, and I update my system almost daily. Looked it up, and turns out the aur manager I use (yay) doesn't update -git packages by default *face-palm*.\n\nSorry to have wasted your time, and a huge thanks for developing input-remapper. Could barely live without it at this point.\n~I'd need to update the pkgver of the AUR package with every commit for it to update on everyones system, which I don't do because I don't even use arch myself anymore, and I'd need to boot up my vm...~\n\n~Maybe I should add a github action like https://jabeztho.com/blog/automating-aur-package-maintenance-with-github-actions/~\n\nedit: moved to https://github.com/sezanzeb/input-remapper/issues/1227\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/sezanzeb/input-remapper/commit/1999aef33b3f510157f4eccd87a55b44a0254b82"], "created_at": "2025-11-15T11:26:16Z"}
